{"title":"What I’ve been reading","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/887990900/0/marginalrevolution~What-Ive-been-reading.html","date":1714538057000,"content":"<p>Benjamin Nathans, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Success-Our-Hopeless-Cause-Dissident/dp/0691117039/ref=sr_1_1?crid=34RAUEBEIZY3Z&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.yXGww0tWRwzRQ0uLD5WGGjN6l0RX9Zpec20F5EAIAmQ4sVzFpQxTlHwbpviprD_LQqzY9RjjV9KvGM6R5NGrh0D9ueKliMRiqXtMLYDQXMSfKEj9V_cvrqFyeCzxF7y_Ztg7hlbMzVwMqGimKE0lUQ.2VWW2v9M7Ihgx69o4TA3STXCjdsWHeypdbqWyej0VZM&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=to+the+success+of+our+hopeless+cause&amp;qid=1714513849&amp;sprefix=to+the+succ%2Caps%2C74&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">To The Success of Our Hopeless Cause: The Many Lives of the Soviet Dissident Movement</a>.  The definitive book on its topic, consisting largely of profiles of dissidents.  The title is taken from a longstanding dissident toast, and yet they won eventually, sort of.  So your cause isn’t hopeless either.</p>\r\n<p>Scott Hodge, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Taxocracy-What-About-Taxes-Daily/dp/B0CL3BXBVS/ref=sr_1_1?crid=5BNAFOM4TXMO&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.BUjAEWbA5_F1x7niNk0tes-ngxX6C1C5-pt2zw-s3PEtm0HxsXQHto99Nw26DaYepkWPh9_RR6zjbDVjfV9cEETb8BZnD-e53idfdfuLcScz_eklLZ7MlCl2zY5PVlBHwGOgrxdh-LMb9fMvGbn5zdkdmw32N8Aoxm9KWFmUAaQSxER9Gk0FYX525wErGwPjm8P1KqAejw71q0hhNDy8C_XA5ABK40Wm4yJDK3nWb_Q.al-s5bVRUZfpv_sX_3n2bJDCc09lvC_is3XWh56F37Y&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=taxocracy+scott+hodge&amp;qid=1714513884&amp;sprefix=scott+hodge+taxo%2Caps%2C69&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Taxocracy: What You Don’t Know About Taxes &amp; How They Rule Your Daily Life</a>.  An excellent short book on the power of tax incentives, written by the former head of the National Tax Foundation.  Incentives matter!</p>\r\n<p>Alex Christofi has written <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Cypria-Journey-Mediterranean-Alex-Christofi-ebook/dp/B0CCF9M9C7/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1GVY0316UOJV9&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.UWwWnIUlsFPzXzaDr7h-20sg-K8xM40AhZi8VByHWxC8dY34aZVpMknSBNeSjuGiVM63eObfan2x628BqSIM-RY5KR-qQvocaVVcU7eqVzgU5lPXk5Fmn1PeoChr7Osoh-RHaZCKNrU28iCtnFek5W0eO_e8uFehrzY8kSbjiSI8nsCzoLth3Hd_IYQ47RTfwlTOL3BT5YueZzH_VI67-6YBui24Mf6zTz84m6o3_a8.8FotmIbK65VSeiVZf4g0Zd5v4XvEbNYF49QoHYcqSrg&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Cypria%3A+A+Journey+to+the+Heart+of+the+Mediterranean&amp;qid=1714513922&amp;sprefix=cypria+a+journey+to+the+heart+of+the+mediterranean%2Caps%2C64&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Cypria: A Journey to the Heart of the Mediterranean</a>, which is the book I will take to Cyprus when I go there.</p>\r\n<p>Randy Barnett, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Life-Liberty-Making-American-Originalist/dp/1641773774/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3JON7PWVJCAP1&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.OFJX9a5tqHEmiCth4vQ_SagciOBUuIwPvuXBoGuhq_y32ZvW-733ZicWjWPKzKXeyzDF8uzhWBWmoe9dcuF_jA.HqlMWN2cIsHGYfeTxKEOPf3DZH9BueBvqNt3XTYstKc&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=randy+barnett+a+life+for+liberty&amp;qid=1714513957&amp;sprefix=randy+barnett+a+life+for+liberty%2Caps%2C65&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">A Life for Liberty: The Making of an American Originalist</a>, is a 616 pp. well-written memoir of a prominent libertarian legal theorist.</p>\r\n<p>Gregory Makoff, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Default-Landmark-Argentinas-Billion-Restructuring/dp/1647123976/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1OJPLI6R3QYUV&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Zxgs-JvP-SCNAtl2S8BEAypJYPNZqfLmJKH9xOOlH9s.hzigQ9aDTbnyErxvGMx_EVqGOszRi7dYUhxs64Qhv88&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=gregory+makoff+default&amp;qid=1714513998&amp;sprefix=gregory+makoff+default%2Caps%2C66&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Default: The Landmark Court Battle over Argentina’s $100 Billion Debt Restructuring</a>.  This is both a good book on how the law handles sovereign defaults and useful background to what Milei is trying to undo in Argentina.</p>\r\n<p>I’ve also been reading a cluster of books on the history of the transgender movement.  I don’t have a single go-to book to recommend, but you could start with Weininger and Magnus Hirschfeld, who are also interesting representatives of Austro-Hungarian and Germanic culture in the early twentieth century.  Overall, I am surprised how many of the key books are out of print, selling used for <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Christine-Jorgensen-Personal-Autobiography/dp/B000W7GL5E/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3O1312SEEP4G8&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.OBuTkycWOJQ8qXgiApbXxiv6von9j6_NqqUUyClgGuYwQqEnZ8iLe7sqDX9obndGqtt1b9kL9At3UiRic7wEHn8Dq25I3moatYehWeA53Bt8uSnHEhivZhFVj0r42TnZPkAdtUge5XGRJfxsDJyKNDfCYOFh7d7TavtbEjs87hDCAZSranNyFkliApX1O123kCJQADcknUcqRgbxNEOKou4bLPoRf1bn2i4bYF5IlQ0.VHFS0Goc090X6z0r2R_dwctxxGu3SHxeb3KqWVRCuTw&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=christine+jorgensen&amp;qid=1713632235&amp;sprefix=christine+jorgensen%2Caps%2C71&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">high prices on Amazon</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/05/what-ive-been-reading-252.html\">What I’ve been reading</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/887990900/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/887990900/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/887990900/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/887990900/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedb